Key Match Events: Jack Grealish scored in the 18th minute
Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a free-kick in the 74th minute
Declan Rice scored in the 84th minute
Arttu Hoskonen scored for Finland in the 87th minute
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley made six changes from the previous game against Greece
Captain Harry Kane returned from injury to lead the line
England returned to a more conventional formation after the experimental lineup without a main striker against Greece
Post-Match Reflections: Jack Grealish celebrated his goal with a thumb-sucking gesture to celebrate the birth of his daughter
England's interim manager Lee Carsley kept alive England's hopes of automatic promotion to League A of the Nations League

Finland will regret missing chances when England led 1-0, including two from Fredrik Jensen who fired just wide in the first-half and missed a sitter early in the second, flashing the ball over from close range and burying his head in his hands
Miscellaneous Highlights: Dean Henderson conceded a goal despite keeping a clean sheet
The game took place at the Helsinki Olympic Stadium
